HEADWORD: Twinter
<hw>Twin"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>twi-</ets>
two + <ets>winter</ets> winter. See <er>Twice</er>, and
<er>Winter</er>.]</ety> <def>A domestic animal two winters old.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
